  "prompt": "Why do I see numbers and not contacts' names? In WhatsApp?",
  "response": "If you're seeing numbers instead of contacts' names in WhatsApp, it could be due to a few reasons:\n\n1. **Contact Not Saved**: The person's phone number must be saved in your device's contact list to show their name on WhatsApp. If it's not, you'll see the number instead.\n\n2. **App Permissions**: WhatsApp requires permission to access your contacts. If this permission has not been granted, the app won't be able to display names. Check your phone\u2019s settings to ensure that WhatsApp has permission to access your contacts.\n\n3. **Outdated App**: Ensure that you are using the latest version of WhatsApp. An outdated version may have bugs that can affect contact display.\n\n4. **Contacts Sync Issues**: Sometimes, syncing issues can prevent contacts from appearing correctly. You can try refreshing the contact list by going to \"Chats\" in WhatsApp, tapping the three dots (menu), and selecting \"Refresh.\"\n\n5. **Blocked Contacts**: If you\u2019ve blocked a contact, their name may not appear, showing instead the number.\n\n6. **Different Country Codes**: If the contact's number is not saved with the correct country code, WhatsApp may not recognize it properly. Make sure the number format is correct.\n\n7. **Phone System Settings**: Check if there are any settings related to displaying contacts or messaging apps that could affect how names are shown.\n\nTry troubleshooting these areas, and you should be able to see your contacts' names instead of their numbers.",
